summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions and statements on women, peace, and security,
Recalling commitments on women and armed conflict from the Beijing Declaration and Platform for Action and the twenty-third Special Session of the General Assembly,
Bearing in mind the Charter of the United Nations and the primary responsibility of the Security Council for international peace and security,
Expressing concern that civilians, particularly women and children, are adversely affected by armed conflict,
Reaffirming the important role of women in conflict prevention and resolution and peace-building,
Urges Member States to ensure increased representation of women in conflict prevention, management, and resolution;
Encourages the Secretary-General to implement his strategic plan to increase women's participation in conflict resolution and peace processes;
Urges the Secretary-General to appoint more women as special representatives and envoys;
Urges the Secretary-General to expand the role and contribution of women in UN field-based operations;
Incorporate a gender perspective into peacekeeping operations and ensure field operations include a gender component where appropriate;
Requests the Secretary-General to provide training guidelines on women's protection, rights, and needs, and urges Member States to incorporate these into their national training programmes;
Urges Member States to increase support for gender-sensitive training efforts.
